{
  "id": 5068127364186112,
  "name": "AccentColor and AccentColorText system colors",
  "summary": "The AccentColor and AccentColorText system colors can be used in CSS to access the system accent color specified on the user's device.\nThis allows developers to apply native app like styling to their web content in contexts where users expect OS theme integration, such as an installed web application. Users must be in an installed web application on the initial profile to see the system accent color rendered.",
